SIMPLE: lightsome
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lightsome
<hw>Light"some</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧t"s⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having light; lighted; not dark or gloomy;
bright.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>White walls make rooms more <qex>lightsome</qex> than black.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gay; airy; cheering; exhilarating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>lightsome</qex> affection of joy.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Light"some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Light"some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Happiness may walk soberly in dark attire, as well as dance
<qex>lightsomely</qex> in a gala dress.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lights-out</ent>⟦br⟧
